# Reduced operator kernel config for the custom Foundry-Local CUDA nuget package.
#
# Used with build.py --include_ops_by_config to prune CUDA (and CPU) kernel registrations
# down to only the operators required by the target language model, shrinking
# onnxruntime_providers_cuda.dll. See docs/Reduced_Operator_Kernel_build.md.
#
# Generated from a quantized LLM export (ONNX opset 24 + com.microsoft opset 1) and then
# augmented with the internal EP ops below.
#
# IMPORTANT: MemcpyFromHost/MemcpyToHost are registered under the ai.onnx domain but never
# appear in a model graph. The graph partitioner inserts them at execution-provider
# boundaries for host<->device copies, so they MUST be kept or the CUDA session fails.
ai.onnx;1;MemcpyFromHost,MemcpyToHost
ai.onnx;24;Cast,Constant,Gather,Mul,RMSNormalization,ReduceSum,Reshape,Shape,Sigmoid,Sub
com.microsoft;1;GatherBlockQuantized,GroupQueryAttention,MatMulNBits,SkipSimplifiedLayerNormalization
